      "bullets": [
        "Language choices dictate memory safety, compile-time error detection, and runtime overhead, directly reducing production bugs and vulnerability risks.",
        "Language paradigms dictate concurrency models, garbage collection pauses, and execution efficiency across modern multi-core system architectures.",
        "Strong type systems and mature tooling accelerate large-scale codebase refactoring, developer onboarding, and long-term software maintainability."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "I Inspected My Take-Home Interview Project. It Was a Whole Operation",
      "url": "https://citizendot.github.io/articles/fake-job-interview-git-hook-malware/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/5nhto6",
      "score": 23,
      "comments": 2,
      "author": "trousers",
      "published": "2026-07-23T01:54:48Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Attackers deploy trojanized coding assignments and malicious dependencies during fake interviews to compromise developer workstations.",
        "Threats often involve obfuscated post-install scripts, rogue npm or pip packages, and infostealers targeting SSH keys or tokens.",
        "Engineers should inspect dependencies and execute untrusted take-home code exclusively within ephemeral containers or isolated VMs."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "GitHub suddenly rejected my SSH key (the fix was a .pub file?!)",
      "url": "https://thorsell.io/2026/07/21/github-ssh-keys.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/twqtlo",
      "score": 60,
      "comments": 18,
      "author": "GLaDER",
      "published": "2026-07-21T10:11:59Z",
      "bullets": [
        "OpenSSH clients require a local .pub file alongside the private key to properly present public key signatures during GitHub authentication.",
        "Missing .pub files prevent OpenSSH from offering correct key identities, causing unexpected rejection of valid SSH credentials by GitHub.",
        "Maintain matching public key files in ~/.ssh and configure IdentitiesOnly to ensure reliable SSH key selection in automated DevOps pipelines."
      ]
    },
